def reverse_string(s):
    s = s.strip()
    characters = list(s)
    length = len(characters)
    for i in range(length / 2):
        temp = characters[i]
        characters[i] = characters[length - i - 1]
        characters[length - i - 1] = temp
    reversed_string = ''.join(characters)
    return reversed_string
